Skip SDL3's hard X11-or-Wayland-required CMake check for the vendored
SDL3 build (via sdl3-sys's "build-from-source-static" feature).

This fork's target renders through KMS/DRM directly (no X11/Wayland
desktop session involved in actual gameplay - exactly how batocera
normally launches emulators), and SDL3's own configure summary already
shows the kmsdrm/dummy/offscreen video drivers enabled regardless of
X11/Wayland availability. Without this, SDL's cmake/macros.cmake hard-fails
configure ("SDL could not find X11 or Wayland development libraries...
If you really don't need desktop windows, the documentation tells you how
to skip this check") rather than just disabling those two backends, which
otherwise makes gopher64 fail to build in a KMS/DRM-only cross-compile
environment even though nothing gopher64 actually needs is missing.

sdl3-sys exposes this exact skip as its own "sdl-unix-console-build"
Cargo feature (maps to SDL3's own -DSDL_UNIX_CONSOLE_BUILD=ON), see
https://github.com/maia-s/sdl3-sys-rs. --locked only pins dependency
*versions* (Cargo.lock), not feature selection, so adding a feature here
doesn't require touching Cargo.lock.

--- a/Cargo.toml
+++ b/Cargo.toml
@@ -20,6 +20,6 @@
 open = "5.3"
 sha2 = "0.11"
-sdl3-sys = { version = "0.6", features = ["build-from-source-static"] }
+sdl3-sys = { version = "0.6", features = ["build-from-source-static", "sdl-unix-console-build"] }
 sdl3-ttf-sys = { version = "0.6", features = ["build-from-source-static", "no-sdlttf-harfbuzz", "no-sdlttf-plutosvg"] }
 rfd = {version = "0.17", optional = true }
 tokio = {version = "1.46", features = ["rt-multi-thread", "macros", "fs", "process"] }
